						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Because it's only one name table, I will probably go with the method like WJYkK described, but the information you've provided will be of great use to me for other things.</div>
<br />Trust me, there is no reason NOT to use indirect adressing if you're copying more than 256 bytes. Using multiple loops that copies 256 or less bytes will just waste program size for nothing.
<br />Unless you want to do something that executes very fast with unrolled loops or something but you probably don't want to worry about that before doing something pretty advanced.</div>

					
